        <p>Ever wondered what’s powering your favorite Shopify store or that slick website you can’t stop browsing? In the fast-paced world of e-commerce and web design, knowing the tech behind the curtain is like having a superpower. Meet <strong>CRFT Lookup</strong>, the digital detective that uncovers a website’s tech stack, performance stats, and more with just a URL and a bit of swagger.</p>
          <p>With Shopify’s ecosystem boasting over 8,000 apps—everything from email marketing to inventory wizardry—figuring out what’s driving a store’s success used to be a guessing game. Not anymore. CRFT Lookup is here to lift the hood and reveal the engine, whether it’s a Shopify store or any website on the web.</p>

          <h2>Why Playing Tech Detective Matters</h2>
          <p>Before we get into the nitty-gritty of CRFT Lookup’s sleuthing skills, let’s talk about why this matters:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Competitor Espionage</strong>: Want to know how your rival’s store is raking in sales? Their tech stack reveals their strategy—marketing tools, customer retention apps, or maybe some subscription voodoo.</li>
            <li><strong>Rookie Roadmap</strong>: New to Shopify or web-building? See what the pros are using to power their sites and get a head start on your own masterpiece.</li>
            <li><strong>Pro-Level Insights</strong>: Developers and agencies, this one’s for you. Spot trending tools and integrations to make killer recommendations that wow your clients.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>CRFT Lookup doesn’t just point and say, “There’s an app!” It hands you a full tech dossier—free of charge and with a side of sass.</p>

          <h2>How CRFT Lookup Works Its Magic</h2>
          <p>So, how does CRFT Lookup play tech detective? It’s like a digital forensics expert, analyzing a website’s HTML, JavaScript, response headers, and more. Powered by a database of over 2,500 technology fingerprints, it spins up a headless Chromium instance to scan any URL you throw its way. In seconds, it identifies frameworks, CMS platforms, analytics tools, and—yes—Shopify apps like Klaviyo, Judge.me, or ReCharge.</p>
          <p>Enter a Shopify store’s URL, and CRFT Lookup will sniff out the apps leaving public-facing clues in the code. It’s not just about Shopify, though—this tool can dissect any website, from TailwindCSS to GitHub, revealing the tech stack in a neat, easy-to-read breakdown.</p>

          <h2>Beyond Apps: The Full Tech Takedown</h2>
          <p>CRFT Lookup isn’t a one-trick pony. It goes way beyond spotting Shopify apps, offering a 360-degree view of a website’s tech profile. Here’s what you get:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Tech Stack Breakdown</strong>: From React and NextJS to Cloudflare and AWS, see the frameworks, CMS platforms, and infrastructure powering a site.</li>
            <li><strong>Lighthouse Scores</strong>: Integrated Google Lighthouse metrics grade performance, accessibility, SEO, and best practices. Is that site fast or just flashy? Now you know.</li>
            <li><strong>Meta Tag Previews</strong>: See how a site looks when shared on Google, Facebook, WhatsApp, or Slack. Perfect for ensuring your site’s social glow-up is on point.</li>
            <li><strong>Sitemap Visualization</strong>: Explore a site’s structure with an interactive tree view, revealing page hierarchy and navigation paths. It’s like a map to the website’s soul.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Whether you’re benchmarking your Shopify store against the big dogs or analyzing a competitor’s site, these insights help you spot gaps, steal ideas (ethically, of course), and optimize like a pro.</p>

          <h2>Real-World Superpowers</h2>
          <p>So, what can you <em>do</em> with all this intel? Plenty:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Merchants</strong>: Compare your tech stack to industry leaders and plug any holes in your setup.</li>
            <li><strong>Marketers</strong>: Discover which tools power your niche’s top campaigns and add them to your arsenal.</li>
            <li><strong>Developers</strong>: Spot integration patterns and trending tech to build smarter solutions.</li>
            <li><strong>Consultants</strong>: Walk into client meetings with data-driven recommendations that scream expertise.</li>
          </ul>
