          <h2>Keeping It Ethical (and Free!)</h2>
          <p>Let’s address the elephant in the room: CRFT Lookup only scans publicly accessible data. No sneaking into private code or spilling sensitive secrets—it’s all above board, analyzing what’s already out there. Think of it as reading the label on a jar, not cracking it open.</p>
          <p>Oh, and did we mention it’s <em>free</em>? Yup, unlimited scans, no credit card required. How do they make money? By selling top-notch web design and development services, not by nickel-and-diming you for reports. Reports are shareable via unique URLs, saved for 30 days, and packed with all the juicy details—perfect for collaborating with your team or impressing a client.</p>

          <h2>The Fine Print on Shopify App Detection</h2>
          <p>Now, to clear up any confusion: CRFT Lookup doesn’t provide detailed app descriptions, pricing, or specific roles in the Shopify ecosystem for detected apps. Instead, it identifies the apps (like Klaviyo or Privy) and categorizes them based on their technical signatures. For deeper insights, you’ll need to research the apps yourself—but CRFT gives you the starting point.</p>
          <p>Its accuracy is solid, thanks to a regularly updated detection engine that cross-references multiple indicators. However, it can only spot apps with public-facing components—custom or heavily obfuscated setups might slip through.</p>

